<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="55.[151,523,969,995]" box="[151,523,969,995]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,523,969,995]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,523,969,995]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1817" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1817" box="[238,523,969,995]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,336,969,995]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Hycleus</emphasis>
Latreille, 1817
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1437,1039,1640]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
The value of the speciose genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1817" box="[537,627,1040,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[537,627,1040,1064]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Hycleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(about 450 species) was debated for a long time and it was recently supported by both morphological (see for a synthesis: 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna" box="[799,965,1076,1101]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Bologna, M. A. (1991) Coleoptera Meloidae. Fauna d'Italia. XXVIII. Calderini, Bologna, XIV + 541 pp." type="book" year="1991">Bologna 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna" box="[982,1252,1076,1101]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Bologna, M. A. &amp; Pinto, J. D. (2002) The Old World genera of Meloidae (Coleoptera): a key and synopsis. Journal of Natural History, 36, 2013 - 2102. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930110062318" type="journal article" year="2002">Bologna &amp; Pinto 2002</bibRefCitation>
) and molecular evidences (Bologna 
<emphasis box="[383,442,1112,1136]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">et al.</emphasis>
2005, 2008c; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pan" box="[607,784,1112,1136]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Pan, Z., Ren, G. - D., Wang, X. - P. &amp; Bologna, M. A. (2013) Revision of the genus Pseudabris Fairmaire (Coleoptera, Meloidae), an endemic to the Tibetan Plateau, with biogeographic comments. Systematic Entomology, 38, 134 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.2012.00651. x" type="journal article" year="2013">
Pan 
<emphasis box="[658,716,1112,1136]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
; Salvi 
<emphasis box="[864,929,1112,1136]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">et al.,</emphasis>
in preparation). Three sections of the genus were described in the literature (
<bibRefCitation author="Pardo" box="[528,758,1148,1173]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Pardo Alcaide, A. (1954) Etudes sur les Meloidae. V. Les Mylabrini du Maroc et du Sahara occidental espagnol (Col. Meloidae). Bulletin de la Societe de Sciences naturelles et physiques du Maroc, 34, 55 - 88." type="journal article" year="1954">Pardo Alcaide,1954</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Alcaide" box="[773,832,1148,1173]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Pardo Alcaide, A. (1955) Estudios sobre Meloidae VI. Sobre algunos Mylabris (s. lat.) de la region etiopica Bulletin de l'Institut royal de Sciences naturelles du Belgique, 31 (49), 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1955">1955</bibRefCitation>
), primarily based on the shape of the mesosternum: without (
<emphasis box="[258,418,1184,1208]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Mesogorbatus</emphasis>
), or with a small (
<emphasis box="[650,814,1184,1207]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Mesotaeniatus</emphasis>
) or wide (
<emphasis box="[945,1097,1185,1208]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Mesoscutatus</emphasis>
) modified fore area, usually named “mesosternal scutum”. These sections are greatly heterogeneous and were not considered as subgenera by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna" box="[151,423,1255,1280]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Bologna, M. A. &amp; Pinto, J. D. (2002) The Old World genera of Meloidae (Coleoptera): a key and synopsis. Journal of Natural History, 36, 2013 - 2102. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930110062318" type="journal article" year="2002">Bologna &amp; Pinto (2002)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna" box="[477,758,1255,1280]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Bologna, M. A. &amp; Turco, F. (2007) The Meloidae (Coleoptera) of the United Arab Emirates with an updating of the Arabian checklist. Zootaxa, 1625, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="2007">Bologna &amp; Turco (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, who preferred consider them as phyletic macro-lineages. In particular, the distinction between the species having a wide (
<emphasis box="[841,993,1293,1316]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Mesoscutatus</emphasis>
) or a narrow (
<emphasis box="[1155,1318,1293,1316]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Mesotaeniatus</emphasis>
) modified fore area of mesosternum is very scarce.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1437,1039,1640]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Several well defined groups of species can be recognized inside each macro-lineage according to the shape of head and mandibles, that of male maxillae and palpomeres, the structure of antennomeres, pronotum and mesopleures, the number and position of penis hooks. Some Palaerctic and Afrotropical groups of species were defined and discussed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pardo" box="[452,694,1471,1496]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Pardo Alcaide, A. (1954) Etudes sur les Meloidae. V. Les Mylabrini du Maroc et du Sahara occidental espagnol (Col. Meloidae). Bulletin de la Societe de Sciences naturelles et physiques du Maroc, 34, 55 - 88." type="journal article" year="1954">Pardo Alcaide (1954</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Alcaide" box="[709,767,1471,1496]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Pardo Alcaide, A. (1955) Estudios sobre Meloidae VI. Sobre algunos Mylabris (s. lat.) de la region etiopica Bulletin de l'Institut royal de Sciences naturelles du Belgique, 31 (49), 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1955">1955</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Alcaide" box="[782,853,1471,1496]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Pardo Alcaide, A. (1958 a) Etudes sur les Meloidae (Col.). IX. Observations sur quelques Mylabris (s. l.) des regions ethiopienne et orientale. Bulletin de l'Institut royal des Sciences naturelles de Belgique, 35 (13), 1 - 39." type="journal article" year="1958" yearSuffix="a">1958a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Alcaide" box="[868,941,1471,1496]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Pardo Alcaide, A. (1958 b) Etudes sur Meloidae (Col.) X. Quelques Mylabris nouveaux ou interessants de la faune ethiopienne. Bollettino del Museo civico di Storia naturale di Trieste, 21, 63 - 76." type="journal article" year="1958" yearSuffix="b">1958b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Alcaide" box="[955,1014,1471,1496]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Pardo Alcaide, A. (1963) Coleopteres Meloides recoltes par M. J. Mateu dans l'Ennedi et au Tchad. Etudes sur les Meloidae, XII. Bulletin de l'Institut fondamental de l'Afrique Noire, (A), 25, 572 - 588." type="journal article" year="1963">1963</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Alcaide" box="[1029,1088,1471,1496]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Pardo Alcaide, A. (1966) Contribution a le faune du Congo (Brazzaville). Mission A. Villiers et A. Descarpentries. XXX. Coleopteres Meloidae. Bulletin de l'Institut fondamental de l'Afrique Noire, (A), 38, 1196 - 1207." type="journal article" year="1966">1966</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Alcaide" box="[1102,1161,1471,1496]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Pardo Alcaide, A. (1968) Etude sur les Meloidae. XX. Sur le Genre Gorrizia Pardo et une nouvelle espece soudanaise du group du brunnipes (Klug). EOS, Revista Espanola de Entomologia, 43, 623 - 629." type="journal article" year="1968">1968</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Alcaide" box="[1176,1236,1471,1496]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Pardo Alcaide, A. (1969) Etudes sur les Meloidae. XXI. Materiaux pour une revision des Mylabrides de l'Afrique du Nord et du Moyen orient (2 e partie). EOS, Revista Espanola de Entomologia, 54, 367 - 376." type="journal article" year="1969">1969</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna" box="[1258,1431,1471,1496]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Bologna, M. A. (1978) Alcuni Meloidi dell'Africa orientale e meridionale e descrizione di una specie nuova (Coleoptera, Meloidae). Zoological researches in Ethiopia, Part I. Quaderni dell'Accademia Nazionale dei Lincei, Roma, 243 (1), 137 - 189." type="journal article" year="1978">Bologna (1978</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna" box="[151,210,1508,1532]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Bologna, M. A. (1979) Meloidae di Turchia. I Contributo (Coleoptera). Fragmenta Entomologica, 15, 143 - 199." type="journal article" year="1979">1979</bibRefCitation>
, 1990, 1991, 1994), and 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna" box="[487,769,1508,1533]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Bologna, M. A. &amp; Turco, F. (2007) The Meloidae (Coleoptera) of the United Arab Emirates with an updating of the Arabian checklist. Zootaxa, 1625, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="2007">Bologna &amp; Turco (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. We define here new Afrotropical groups of species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1437,1039,1640]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Most African species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1817" box="[495,585,1544,1568]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[495,585,1544,1568]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Hycleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been described as 
<emphasis box="[882,1369,1544,1568]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[882,986,1544,1568]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Mylabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mylabris</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harold" authorityYear="1879" box="[1002,1106,1544,1568]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Zonabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Zonabris</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" box="[1123,1210,1544,1567]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Coryna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Coryna</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Voigts" authorityYear="1902" box="[1226,1369,1545,1568]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Decapotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Decapotoma</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. In a preliminary checklist of the Namibian 
<taxonomicName authority=", Bologna (2000 a)" authorityName=", Bologna" authorityYear="2000" box="[594,908,1580,1605]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Meloidae, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna" box="[716,908,1580,1605]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refString="Bologna, M. A. (2000 a) Biodiversity of the Meloidae (Coleoptera) of the Brandberg Massif (Namibia). In: Kirk-Spriggs, A. H. &amp; Marais, E. (Eds.), Daures-Biodiversity of the Brandberg Massif, Namibia. Cimbebasia, Memoir 9, 201 - 208." type="journal article" year="2000" yearSuffix="a">Bologna (2000a)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
defined several new combinations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1817" box="[1346,1436,1580,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1346,1436,1580,1604]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Hycleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species and only new combinations are here provided.
</paragraph>
